## Early game

Voidgel Orb is a **Zariman regional reward**, best farmed at **Tuvul Commons**
running **Void Cascade**. It comes from the mission's end-of-run reward table
with a relatively low fixed chance (roughly 9.76%), so plan on running
several Cascade rotations rather than expecting one per mission.

Because it's a **reward-table roll** rather than an in-mission resource
pickup, a **Resource Drop Booster does not increase your Orb drop rate** —
the only way to get more is to run more (or faster) Void Cascade rotations
and bounties.

## Mid & late game

**Steel Path Tuvul Commons** is the sustained late-game farm: tougher enemies
mean faster, more consistent Cascade rotations, so a full squad can bank more
reward-table rolls per hour. Steel Path doesn't change the reward-table odds
themselves — it just lets you complete more rotations in the same time.
Running full Cascade rotations back-to-back, along with Zariman bounties, is
the most efficient way to stockpile Voidgel Orbs for Zariman gear and
Deimos/Zariman crafting alike.

